MOUNTAIN AND SQUIRREL.

HE mountain and the squirrel

Had a quarrel ; And the- former called the latter “ Little

Prig.’' Bun replied: “ You are doubtless very big ; But all sorts of things and weather

Must be taken in together, To make up a year And a sphere.

And I think it no disgrace

To occupy my place.

If I’m not so large as yon,

You are not so small as I,

And not half so spry.

I’ll not deny you make

A very pretty squirrel track ;
